{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":253,"text":"Basking sharks are awesome creatures."},{"time":2454,"text":"They are just magnificent."},{"time":3801,"text":"They grow 10 meters long; some say bigger."},{"time":7373,"text":"They might weigh up to two tons."},{"time":9412,"text":"Some say up to five tons."},{"time":11000,"text":"They're the second-largest\nfish in the world."},{"time":13277,"text":"They're also harmless\nplankton-feeding animals."},{"time":15913,"text":"And they are thought to be able to filter\na cubic kilometer of water every hour"},{"time":21373,"text":"and can feed on 30 kilos\nof zoo plankton a day to survive."},{"time":26134,"text":"They're fantastic creatures."},{"time":27523,"text":"We're very lucky in Ireland,"},{"time":28904,"text":"we have plenty of basking sharks\nand plenty of opportunities to study them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32508,"text":"They were very important\nto coastal communities,"},{"time":34830,"text":"going back hundreds of years,"},{"time":36290,"text":"especially around\nthe Claddaghduff, Connemara region"},{"time":39066,"text":"where subsistence farmers used to sail\nout on their hookers and open boats,"},{"time":42688,"text":"sometimes way offshore\nto a place called the Sunfish Bank,"},{"time":45439,"text":"about 30 miles west of Achill Island,"},{"time":47240,"text":"to kill the basking sharks."},{"time":48557,"text":"This is a woodcut from about the 1800s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50753,"text":"They were very important,\nfor the oil out of their liver."},{"time":53528,"text":"A third of the basking\nshark's size is their liver,"},{"time":56014,"text":"and it's full of oil, gallons of oil."},{"time":57821,"text":"That oil was used especially for lighting,"},{"time":59934,"text":"but also for dressing wounds\nand other things."},{"time":62131,"text":"In fact, the streetlights in 1742,"},{"time":64041,"text":"of Galway, Dublin and Waterford,"},{"time":65589,"text":"were lit with sunfish oil."},{"time":67000,"text":"\"Sunfish\" is one of the words\nfor basking sharks."},{"time":69414,"text":"So they were incredibly important animals."},{"time":71454,"text":"They've been around a long time,\nvery important to coastal communities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":74847,"text":"Probably the best-documented\nbasking shark fishery in the world"},{"time":78165,"text":"is that from Achill Island."},{"time":79701,"text":"This is Keem Bay up in Achill Island."},{"time":82100,"text":"Sharks used to come into the bay,"},{"time":84277,"text":"and the fishermen\nwould tie a net off the headland,"},{"time":87302,"text":"string it out, an old Manila net,"},{"time":88958,"text":"and as the shark came round,\nit would hit the net,"},{"time":91331,"text":"the net would collapse on it."},{"time":92751,"text":"It would often drown and suffocate."},{"time":94470,"text":"Or at times, they would row out\nin their small curraghs"},{"time":97349,"text":"and kill it with a lance\nthrough the back of the neck."},{"time":99907,"text":"And then they'd tow the sharks\nback to Purteen Harbour,"},{"time":102675,"text":"boil them up, use the oil."},{"time":104423,"text":"They also used the flesh\nas well, for fertilizer"},{"time":108371,"text":"and also would fin the sharks."},{"time":111291,"text":"This is probably the biggest threat\nto sharks worldwide --"},{"time":114156,"text":"the finning of sharks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116219,"text":"We're often frightened\nof sharks, thanks to \"Jaws.\""},{"time":118732,"text":"Maybe five or six people\nget killed by sharks every year."},{"time":121810,"text":"There was someone recently, wasn't there?\nJust a couple weeks ago."},{"time":125009,"text":"We kill about 100 million sharks a year."},{"time":127000,"text":"So I don't know what the balance is,"},{"time":129000,"text":"but I think sharks have more right\nto be fearful of us than we have of them."},{"time":133018,"text":"It was a well-documented fishery."},{"time":134671,"text":"As you can see here,\nit peaked in the '50s,"},{"time":136898,"text":"where they were killing\n1,500 sharks a year."},{"time":139019,"text":"And it declined very fast --\na classic boom-and-bust fishery,"},{"time":141977,"text":"which suggests that a stock\nhas been depleted"},{"time":144673,"text":"or there's low reproductive rates."},{"time":146635,"text":"They killed about 12,000 sharks\nwithin this period,"},{"time":149129,"text":"literally just by stringing a Manila rope"},{"time":152083,"text":"off the tip of Keem Bay\nup in Achill Island."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155177,"text":"Sharks were still killed\nup into the mid-80s,"},{"time":157614,"text":"especially out of places\nlike Dunmore East in County Waterford."},{"time":160651,"text":"About two and a half, 3,000\nsharks were killed up till '85,"},{"time":163504,"text":"mainly by Norwegian vessels."},{"time":165222,"text":"You can't really see,"},{"time":166400,"text":"but these are Norwegian\nbasking shark hunting vessels."},{"time":168963,"text":"The black line in the crow's nest\nsignifies this is a shark vessel,"},{"time":172542,"text":"rather than a whaling vessel."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174638,"text":"The importance of basking sharks\nto the coast communities"},{"time":177507,"text":"is recognized through the language."},{"time":179209,"text":"I don't pretend\nto [know many Irish words],"},{"time":181518,"text":"but in Kerry they were often\nknown as \"ainmhide Na seolta,\""},{"time":185100,"text":"\"the monster with the sails.\""},{"time":187101,"text":"Another title would be \"liop an dá lapa,\""},{"time":190129,"text":"\"the unwieldy beast with two fins.\""},{"time":192820,"text":"\"Liabhán mór,\" suggesting a big animal."},{"time":195859,"text":"Or my favorite, \"liabhán chor gréine,\"\n\"the great fish of the sun.\""},{"time":199386,"text":"That's a lovely, evocative name."},{"time":200946,"text":"On Tory Island -- a strange place\nanyway -- they were known as \"muldoons.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":204500,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":205545,"text":"No one seems to know why."},{"time":206764,"text":"Hope there's no one\nfrom Tory here. Lovely place."},{"time":209123,"text":"But more commonly all around the island,\nthey were known as the sunfish."},{"time":213170,"text":"And this represents their habit\nof basking on the surface"},{"time":215903,"text":"when the sun is out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217085,"text":"There's great concern\nthat basking sharks are depleted"},{"time":219672,"text":"all throughout the world."},{"time":221209,"text":"Some say it's not population decline,"},{"time":223226,"text":"it might be a change\nin the distribution of plankton."},{"time":225739,"text":"It's been suggested"},{"time":226920,"text":"that these sharks would make\nfantastic indicators of climate change,"},{"time":230168,"text":"as they're basically\ncontinuous plankton recorders,"},{"time":232603,"text":"swimming around with their mouth open."},{"time":234447,"text":"They're now listed\nas vulnerable under the IUCN."},{"time":236756,"text":"There's movements in Europe\nto try and stop catching them."},{"time":239740,"text":"There's now a ban on catching\nand even landing them,"},{"time":242220,"text":"even landing ones caught accidentally."},{"time":244309,"text":"They're not protected in Ireland;"},{"time":245921,"text":"in fact, they have no legislative\nstatus in Ireland whatsoever,"},{"time":248930,"text":"despite our importance for the species"},{"time":250884,"text":"and also the historical context\nwithin which basking sharks reside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":254462,"text":"We know very little about them."},{"time":256700,"text":"And most of what we do know"},{"time":258125,"text":"is based on their habit\nof coming to the surface --"},{"time":260935,"text":"we try and guess what they're doing\nfrom their behavior on the surface."},{"time":264361,"text":"I only found out last year,\nat a conference on the Isle of Man,"},{"time":267453,"text":"just how unusual it is to live somewhere"},{"time":270191,"text":"where basking sharks regularly,\nfrequently and predictably"},{"time":273762,"text":"come to the surface to \"bask.\""},{"time":276726,"text":"It's a fantastic opportunity\nfor a scientist"},{"time":278845,"text":"to see and experience basking sharks."},{"time":280670,"text":"They are awesome creatures."},{"time":282043,"text":"It gives us a fantastic opportunity\nto study them, to get access to them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285523,"text":"What we've been doing for a couple\nyears -- last year was a big year --"},{"time":288945,"text":"is we started tagging sharks,"},{"time":290823,"text":"so we could try to get some idea\nof sight fidelity and movement"},{"time":293893,"text":"and things like that."},{"time":295075,"text":"So we concentrated mainly\nin North Donegal and West Kerry"},{"time":298400,"text":"as the two areas\nwhere I was mainly active."},{"time":301135,"text":"And we tagged them\nvery simply, not very high-tech,"},{"time":305316,"text":"with a big, long pole."},{"time":306516,"text":"This is a beachcaster rod\nwith a tag on the end."},{"time":309166,"text":"You go up in your boat and tag the shark."},{"time":312599,"text":"And we were very effective."},{"time":314171,"text":"We tagged 105 sharks last summer."},{"time":317033,"text":"We got 50 in three days\noff Inishowen Peninsula."}]},{"cues":[{"time":320708,"text":"Half the challenge to get access"},{"time":322289,"text":"is to be in the right place\nat the right time."},{"time":324527,"text":"But it's a very simple, easy technique;\nI'll show you what it looks like."},{"time":328020,"text":"We use a pole camera on the boat\nto actually film the shark."},{"time":330895,"text":"One, it's to try and work out\nthe gender of the shark."},{"time":333456,"text":"We also deployed some satellite tags,\nso we did use high-tech stuff as well."},{"time":337143,"text":"These are archival tags."},{"time":338476,"text":"What they do is store the data."},{"time":340439,"text":"A satellite tag only works\nwhen the air is clear of the water"},{"time":343349,"text":"and can send a signal to the satellite."},{"time":345270,"text":"And sharks and fish\nare underwater most of the time,"},{"time":347749,"text":"so this tag actually works out\nthe locations of shark,"},{"time":350702,"text":"depending on the timing\nand the setting of the sun,"},{"time":354088,"text":"plus water temperature and depth."},{"time":356063,"text":"And you have to kind of\nreconstruct the path."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358255,"text":"What happens is,"},{"time":359452,"text":"you set the tag to detach\nfrom the shark after a fixed period --"},{"time":362566,"text":"in this case, eight months --"},{"time":363988,"text":"and literally to the day,\nthe tag popped off,"},{"time":366120,"text":"drifted up, said hello to the satellite"},{"time":368023,"text":"and sent, not all the data,\nbut enough data for us to use."},{"time":370916,"text":"This is the only way to really work out\ntheir behavior and movements"},{"time":374184,"text":"when they're underwater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376277,"text":"And here's a couple\nof maps that we've done."},{"time":378400,"text":"In that one, you can see\nthat we tagged both off Kerry."},{"time":381580,"text":"Basically, it spent all its time,\nthe last eight months, in Irish waters."},{"time":385089,"text":"On Christmas, it was out\non the shelf edge."},{"time":387122,"text":"Here's one we haven't ground-truthed yet"},{"time":389090,"text":"with sea-surface temperature\nand water depth,"},{"time":391239,"text":"but again, the second shark\nspent most of its time"},{"time":393616,"text":"in and around the Irish Sea."},{"time":394989,"text":"Colleagues from the Isle of Man\nlast year actually tagged one shark"},{"time":398191,"text":"that went from the Isle of Man\nto Nova Scotia in about 90 days."},{"time":401399,"text":"Nine and a half thousand kilometers --\nwe never thought that happened."}]},{"cues":[{"time":404746,"text":"Another colleague in the States\ntagged about 20 sharks off Massachusetts."},{"time":408694,"text":"His tags didn't really work."},{"time":410158,"text":"All he knows is where he tagged them,"},{"time":412015,"text":"and where they popped off."},{"time":413507,"text":"His tags popped off in the Caribbean,"},{"time":415849,"text":"and even in Brazil."},{"time":417400,"text":"We thought basking sharks\nwere temperate animals"},{"time":419739,"text":"and lived in our latitudes,"},{"time":421255,"text":"but in actual fact, they're obviously\ncrossing the equator as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424471,"text":"So very simple things like that,"},{"time":426257,"text":"we're trying to learn\nabout basking sharks."},{"time":429088,"text":"One thing that I think\nis a very surprising and strange thing"},{"time":433685,"text":"is just how low the genetic\ndiversity of sharks is."},{"time":436674,"text":"I'm not a geneticist, so I won't pretend\nto understand the genetics."},{"time":440159,"text":"And that's why it's great\nto have collaboration."},{"time":442540,"text":"Whereas I'm a field person,"},{"time":443876,"text":"I get panic attacks"},{"time":445424,"text":"if I have to spend too many hours\nin a lab with a white coat on."},{"time":448596,"text":"Take me away."},{"time":449851,"text":"So we can work with geneticists\nwho understand that."},{"time":452455,"text":"So when they looked at\nthe genetics of basking sharks,"},{"time":455059,"text":"they found that the diversity\nwas incredibly low."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458092,"text":"If you look at the first line, really,"},{"time":459975,"text":"you can see that all these different\nshark species are all quite similar."},{"time":463455,"text":"I think this means they're all sharks"},{"time":465257,"text":"and they've come from a common ancestry."},{"time":467211,"text":"But if you look at nucleotide diversity,"},{"time":469305,"text":"which is more genetics\nthat are passed on through the parents,"},{"time":472549,"text":"you see that basking sharks,\nif you look at the first study,"},{"time":475406,"text":"was order of magnitude less diverse\neven than other shark species."},{"time":479400,"text":"You can see this work\nwas only done in 2006."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481496,"text":"Before 2006, we had no idea of the genetic\nvariability of basking sharks."},{"time":485157,"text":"We had no idea: Did they distinguish\ninto different populations?"},{"time":488294,"text":"Were there subpopulations?"},{"time":489593,"text":"And that's very important\nif you want to know"},{"time":491768,"text":"what the population size is,\nand the status of the animals."},{"time":494569,"text":"So, Les Noble in Aberdeen kind of found\nthis a bit unbelievable, really."},{"time":498204,"text":"So he did another study\nusing microsatellites,"},{"time":504813,"text":"which is much more expensive,\nmuch more time-consuming,"},{"time":507448,"text":"and to his surprise,\ncame up with almost identical results."}]},{"cues":[{"time":510733,"text":"So it does seem to be\nthat basking sharks, for some reason,"},{"time":513669,"text":"have incredibly low diversity."},{"time":515463,"text":"And it's thought maybe\nit was a genetic bottleneck,"},{"time":517981,"text":"thought to have been 12,000 years ago,"},{"time":520076,"text":"and this has caused a very low diversity."},{"time":522624,"text":"And yet, if you look at the whale shark,"},{"time":524608,"text":"which is the other\nplankton-eating large shark,"},{"time":527347,"text":"its diversity is much greater."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528842,"text":"So it doesn't really make sense at all."},{"time":531301,"text":"They found that there was\nno genetic differentiation"},{"time":533759,"text":"between any of the world's oceans\nof basking sharks:"},{"time":536244,"text":"even though they're found\nthroughout the world,"},{"time":538506,"text":"you couldn't tell\nthe difference, genetically,"},{"time":540688,"text":"from one from the Pacific, Atlantic,\nNew Zealand, Ireland, South Africa."},{"time":544145,"text":"They all basically seem the same."},{"time":545748,"text":"Which, again, is kind of surprising;\nyou wouldn't expect that."},{"time":548677,"text":"I don't understand or pretend\nto understand this;"},{"time":551048,"text":"I suspect most geneticists don't either,"},{"time":552982,"text":"but they produce the numbers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":554400,"text":"So you can actually estimate\nthe population size"},{"time":556751,"text":"based on the diversity of the genetics."},{"time":558945,"text":"And Rus Hoelzel came up with\nan effective population size:"},{"time":562521,"text":"8,200 animals."},{"time":564378,"text":"That's it -- 8,000 animals in the world."},{"time":567306,"text":"You're thinking,\n\"That's ridiculous. No way.\""},{"time":569552,"text":"So Les did a finer study,"},{"time":571400,"text":"and he found out it came out about 9,000."},{"time":574202,"text":"Using different microsatellites\ngave the different results,"},{"time":577107,"text":"but the mean of all these\nstudies is about 5,000,"},{"time":581772,"text":"which I personally don't believe."},{"time":583400,"text":"But then, I am a skeptic."},{"time":585054,"text":"But even if you toss a few numbers around,"},{"time":587507,"text":"you're probably talking an effective\npopulation of about 20,000 animals."},{"time":590948,"text":"Do you remember how many they killed\noff Achill in the 70s and the 50s?"},{"time":595487,"text":"So what it tells us, actually,"},{"time":597207,"text":"is that there's actually a risk\nof extinction of this species"},{"time":600483,"text":"because its population is so small."},{"time":602400,"text":"In fact, of those 20,000,"},{"time":603955,"text":"8,000 were thought to be females."},{"time":606147,"text":"There's only 8,000 basking shark\nfemales in the world?"},{"time":608858,"text":"I don't know. I don't believe it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611125,"text":"The problem with this\nis they were constrained with samples."},{"time":614792,"text":"They didn't get enough samples"},{"time":616399,"text":"to really explore the genetics\nin enough detail."},{"time":620714,"text":"So, where do you get samples from\nfor your genetic analysis?"},{"time":625670,"text":"Well, one obvious source is dead sharks --"},{"time":628482,"text":"dead sharks, washed up."},{"time":629758,"text":"We might get two or three dead sharks\nwashed up in Ireland a year,"},{"time":633038,"text":"if we're kind of lucky."},{"time":634584,"text":"Another source would be\nfisheries' bycatch."},{"time":636958,"text":"We were getting quite a few caught\nin surface drift nets."},{"time":639971,"text":"That's banned now, and that'll be\ngood news for the sharks."},{"time":642781,"text":"And some are caught in nets, in trawls."},{"time":644722,"text":"This is a shark that was actually\nlanded in Howth just before Christmas --"},{"time":648364,"text":"illegally, because you're not allowed\nto do that under EU law --"},{"time":651415,"text":"and was actually sold\nfor eight euros a kilo as shark steak."},{"time":654277,"text":"They even put a recipe up on the wall,"},{"time":656125,"text":"until they were told it was illegal."},{"time":657927,"text":"They actually did get a fine for that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659830,"text":"So if you look at\nall those studies I showed you,"},{"time":662180,"text":"the total number of samples worldwide"},{"time":664860,"text":"is 86, at present."},{"time":666858,"text":"So it's very important work,"},{"time":668974,"text":"and they can ask\nsome really good questions,"},{"time":671093,"text":"and tell us about population size\nand subpopulations and structure,"},{"time":675400,"text":"but they're constrained\nby lack of samples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678744,"text":"When we were out tagging our sharks --"},{"time":680617,"text":"this is how we tagged them on the front\nof a RIB, get in there fast --"},{"time":683951,"text":"occasionally, the sharks do react."},{"time":686141,"text":"On one occasion, when we were\nup in Malin Head in Donegal,"},{"time":688916,"text":"the shark smacked the side\nof the boat with his tail,"},{"time":691438,"text":"more, I think, in startle to the fact\nthat a boat came near it,"},{"time":694606,"text":"rather than the tag going in."},{"time":696957,"text":"And that was fine. We got wet. No problem."},{"time":699876,"text":"And then when myself and Emmett\ngot back to Malin Head, to the pier,"},{"time":703890,"text":"I noticed some black slime\non the front of the boat."},{"time":706356,"text":"I used to spend a lot of time\non commercial fishing boats,"},{"time":709109,"text":"and I remember fishermen saying"},{"time":710612,"text":"they can tell when a basking shark\nhas been caught in a net,"},{"time":713459,"text":"because it leaves a black slime behind."},{"time":715363,"text":"So that must have come from the shark."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717218,"text":"Now, we had an interest\nin getting tissue samples for genetics"},{"time":720636,"text":"because we knew they were very valuable."},{"time":722646,"text":"We would use conventional methods;"},{"time":724327,"text":"I have a crossbow --\nyou see it in my hand there,"},{"time":726668,"text":"which we use to sample whales\nand dolphins for genetic studies as well."},{"time":730178,"text":"So I tried that, I tried many techniques."},{"time":732177,"text":"All it was doing was breaking my arrows,"},{"time":734130,"text":"because the shark's skin\nis just so strong."},{"time":736179,"text":"There was no way we were going\nto get a sample from that."},{"time":738979,"text":"That wasn't going to work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740580,"text":"So when I saw the black slime\non the bow of the boat,"},{"time":743161,"text":"I thought, \"If you take\nwhat you're given in this world ...\""},{"time":746162,"text":"So I scraped it off."},{"time":747350,"text":"I had a little tube with alcohol in it\nto send to the geneticists."},{"time":751769,"text":"So I scraped the slime off\nand sent it to Aberdeen,"},{"time":754848,"text":"and said, \"You might try that.\""},{"time":756388,"text":"And they sat on it for months."},{"time":758022,"text":"It was only because we had\na conference on the Isle of Man."},{"time":760858,"text":"But I kept emailing Les, saying,"},{"time":762421,"text":"\"Have you had a chance\nto look at my slime?\""},{"time":764540,"text":"And he was like, \"Yeah, yeah. Later.\""},{"time":766407,"text":"He thought he'd better do it\nbecause I never met him before;"},{"time":769254,"text":"he might lose face if he hadn't done\nthe thing I sent him."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772033,"text":"And he was amazed that they actually\ngot DNA from the slime."},{"time":774908,"text":"They amplified it and they tested it,"},{"time":776767,"text":"and they found, yes,\nthis was actually basking shark DNA,"},{"time":779589,"text":"which was got from the slime."},{"time":782568,"text":"So he was very excited."},{"time":783757,"text":"It became known as \"Simon's shark slime.\""},{"time":787066,"text":"And I thought, \"Hey, you know,\nI can build on this.\""},{"time":789981,"text":"So we thought, OK, we're going to try\nto get out and get some slime."},{"time":793767,"text":"So having spent three-and-a-half\nthousand on satellite tags ..."},{"time":799987,"text":"I then thought I'd invest 7.95 --\nthe price is still on it --"},{"time":803448,"text":"in my local hardware store in Kilrush"},{"time":805662,"text":"for a mop handle,"},{"time":807456,"text":"and even less money on some oven cleaners."},{"time":810400,"text":"And I wrapped the oven cleaner\naround the edge of the mop handle"},{"time":813895,"text":"and ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":815400,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":816982,"text":"I was desperate to have an opportunity\nto get some sharks."},{"time":820537,"text":"And this was into August now,\nand normally sharks peak in June, July,"},{"time":824954,"text":"and you rarely see them,\nor rarely can be in the right place"},{"time":827967,"text":"to find sharks into August."},{"time":829542,"text":"We were desperate,\nso we rushed out to the Blaskets"},{"time":831996,"text":"as soon as we heard\nthere were sharks there,"},{"time":834090,"text":"and managed to find some sharks."},{"time":835641,"text":"So by just rubbing\nthe mop handle down the shark"},{"time":839129,"text":"as it swam under the boat --"},{"time":840721,"text":"you see a shark\nrunning under the boat here --"},{"time":843255,"text":"we managed to collect slime."},{"time":844621,"text":"And here it is."},{"time":845893,"text":"Look at that lovely black shark slime."},{"time":849646,"text":"And in about half an hour,\nwe got five samples."},{"time":854263,"text":"Five individual sharks were sampled"},{"time":856040,"text":"using Simon's Shark Slime Sampling System."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858896,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":860735,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":866090,"text":"I've been working on whales and dolphins\nin Ireland for 20 years now,"},{"time":869368,"text":"and they're a bit more dramatic."},{"time":870931,"text":"You probably saw\nthe humpback whale footage"},{"time":872991,"text":"we got a month or two ago\noff County Wexford."},{"time":875125,"text":"And you always think\nyou might have some legacy"},{"time":877399,"text":"you can leave the world behind,"},{"time":878917,"text":"and I was thinking of humpback\nwhales breaching and dolphins."},{"time":881876,"text":"But hey -- sometimes\nthese things are sent to you"},{"time":884285,"text":"and you just have to take them\nwhen they come."},{"time":886501,"text":"So this is possibly\ngoing to be my legacy --"},{"time":888622,"text":"Simon's Shark Slime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":890288,"text":"We got more money this year"},{"time":891946,"text":"to carry on collecting\nmore and more samples."},{"time":894591,"text":"One thing that is very useful\nis that we use a pole camera --"},{"time":897555,"text":"this is my colleague, Joanne,\nwith a pole camera --"},{"time":899992,"text":"where you can look underneath the shark."},{"time":901955,"text":"What you're trying to look at is,\nthe males have claspers,"},{"time":904748,"text":"which kind of dangle out\nbehind the back of the shark."},{"time":907392,"text":"So you can quite easily tell\nthe gender of the shark."},{"time":910013,"text":"If we can tell the gender of the shark\nbefore we sample it,"},{"time":913784,"text":"we can tell the geneticist\nthis was taken from a male or a female."},{"time":916915,"text":"Because in the moment,\nthey have no way, genetically,"},{"time":919442,"text":"of telling the difference\nbetween a male and a female,"},{"time":922004,"text":"which I find staggering,"},{"time":923187,"text":"because they don't know\nwhat primers to look for."},{"time":925796,"text":"Being able to tell the gender of a shark"},{"time":928134,"text":"is very important\nfor things like policing the trade"},{"time":932400,"text":"in basking shark and other species\nthrough the sightings,"},{"time":936820,"text":"because it is illegal\nto trade in these sharks."},{"time":939059,"text":"And they are caught and are on the market."}]},{"cues":[{"time":941121,"text":"So as a field biologist,"},{"time":942516,"text":"you just want to get encounters\nwith these animals,"},{"time":944986,"text":"and learn as much as you can."},{"time":946400,"text":"They're often quite brief,\nthey're often very seasonally constrained."},{"time":949834,"text":"You just want to learn as much\nas you can as soon as you can."},{"time":952763,"text":"But isn't it fantastic"},{"time":954554,"text":"that you can then offer\nthese samples and opportunities"},{"time":958077,"text":"to other disciplines,\nsuch as the geneticists,"},{"time":960921,"text":"who can gain so much more from that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":963400,"text":"So as I said, these things\nare sent to you in strange ways."},{"time":967130,"text":"Grab them while you can."},{"time":968400,"text":"I'll take that as my scientific legacy."},{"time":970366,"text":"Hopefully, I might get something\na bit more dramatic and romantic"},{"time":973477,"text":"before I die."},{"time":974750,"text":"But for the time being,\nthank you for that."},{"time":977179,"text":"And keep an eye out for sharks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":978689,"text":"If you're more interested, we have\na basking shark website now set up."},{"time":982459,"text":"So thank you and thank you for listening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984453,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}